	section.center
		p Verticator shows vertical indicators
	section.center
		p On vertical slides only
	section.center
		p If you do not override the colors in the options, Verticator will use your theme colors: the bullets will be the same color as text in your presentation.
		p.small The theme color is set as a CSS variable (#[code --c-theme-color]) in the Reveal element, and can also be used by other elements. On this page, it is #[code rgb(255, 255, 255)], because that is also the text color.
	section.center(data-background="silver")
		p Verticator detects if the slide background is set to a different color. If you do not override the colors in the options, the bullets will still take on the heading- or textcolor of the slide.
		p.small On this page, the CSS variable (#[code --c-theme-color]) is #[code rgb(34, 34, 34)], because that is also the text color.
	section.center(data-background="silver")
		p Verticator also fixes the appearance of text inside double opposite backgrounds, for example when the theme is dark, the stack is light and the slide is dark again.
	section.center
		p Verticator is configurable globally through the Reveal options, but the colors can also be changed per slide.

